<HEADLINE>
FT  28 JAN 93 / Parliament and Politics: Major sees upturn in confidence
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RALPH ATKINS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MR JOHN MAJOR said last night that Britain was set for a 'decisive move'
towards economic growth, Ralph Atkins writes.
He told UK businessmen in Bombay that confidence 'is beginning to return to
housebuyers, consumers and investors'. Inflation was at its lowest for 6 1/2
years, interest rates were at their lowest for 15 years and the sterling
exchange rate was 'highly competitive'.
His upbeat comments were coupled with a promise that 'the government will be
working closely with industry, especially manufacturing companies, to
maximise investment in modern equipment'.
Mr Major has signalled that he is prepared to listen more to businessmen -
and his comments could have been a hint of extra help for industry in the
March Budget.
</TEXT>
