FT  28 JAN 93 / Infant deaths decline
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
ALTHOUGH it has fallen by a third since 1981, Britain's infant mortality
record remains in the middle of the European league. It continues to reflect
social class, with rates much higher for babies born to parents in the
unskilled and semi-skilled social groups.
