<HEADLINE>
FT  28 JAN 93 / Births outside marriage increase
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALAN PIKE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE UPWARD trend in births outside marriage is continuing, Alan Pike writes.
By 1991 three in 10 births were to unmarried women, which was double the
proportion 10 years earlier. Half of the births are registered with both
parents living at the same address.
The issue is one that produces remarkable variations between European
countries. Half of all births in Sweden are outside marriage compared with
only one in 50 in Greece.
</TEXT>
