<HEADLINE>
FT  28 JAN 93 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
This weeks British interest rate reduction, and its accompanying currency
disturbances, have had not had the effect of enlivening wool textile trade.
There is more interest in how prices may have been affected, but not to the
point of placing business. The firming effect is very slight because of
continuing difficult and competitive conditions throughout Europe.
Australian and most world wool values meanwhile only manage to drift along
without clear trend. The AWC market indicator was down to 502 cents a kg. on
January 27, compared with 509 a week before.
