FT  28 JAN 93 / UK Company News: Worthington trimmed to Pounds 0.3m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Worthington Group suffered a decline in profits to Pounds 305,000 in the
first half, because of difficulties within the button wholesaling business
and the trimmings operation.
On increased sales of Pounds 7.3m (Pounds 6.11m) in the six months to
September 30, pre-tax profits fell 39 per cent from a previous Pounds
496,000.
