<HEADLINE>
FT  28 JAN 93 / UK Company News: Sea Containers expects an increase to
Dollars 2.25 in earnings per share
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MATTHEW CURTIN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
SEA CONTAINERS, the Bermuda-based cargo equipment and ferry group, has
forecast an increase in earnings per share from Dollars 1.95 to between
Dollars 2.10 and Dollars 2.25 in the year ended December 31 1992.
In addition, the group is pressing ahead with plans to sell a second Dollars
25m tranche of senior subordinated debentures as part of an overall plan to
sell Dollars 125m as it raises funds to expand its container and high-speed
ferry operations.
Mr James Sherwood, chairman, said the group's fourth quarter results would
show a modest profit against Dollars 0.40 loss per share in the same period
in 1991.
SeaCon reported pre-tax profits of Dollars 28.5m (Dollars 27.6m) in the
September quarter.
He noted that 1991 earnings included a Dollars 0.62 per share contribution
from an Dollars 6.2m out-of-court settlement with British Rail.
SeaCon entered litigation with BR over a dispute regarding reciprocal travel
arrangements after the container group acquired Sealink in 1984.
Mr Sherwood said that the group expected earnings this year would be higher
than last year's 'in view of our rapidly expanding marine container leasing
business and imp-roved ferry fleet deploy-ment'.
Improving market conditions for high-yield bonds in the US had allowed the
group to proceed with the total debenture sale, after poorer conditions
limited the sale to Dollars 100m on November 19 last year.
