<HEADLINE>
FT  27 JAN 93 / The Lex Column: IBM
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The departure of Mr John Akers from the helm of IBM may be a shock, but it
is not a revolution. Mr Akers is still expected to pick an insider to
succeed him. Further pain may be necessary before the company fully accepts
its reduced role in a cost-efficient world where computers are commodities.
</TEXT>
