FT  27 JAN 93 / Court rules victims of 1984 Indian gas disaster cannot
challenge settlement in America
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
A US federal appeals court ruled yesterday that victims of the 1984 poison
gas disaster in Bhopal, India, cannot challenge in America the Dollars 470m
(Pounds 309.2m) settlement between the Indian government and Union Carbide,
Reuter reports from New York. It upheld a ruling that the Indian government
had the right to negotiate the settlement with the chemical company, based
in Danbury, Connecticut, from whose plant the gas leaked and that the
victims had no standing in the US.
